This paper is a quite good citation on the age face progression.
This is an interesting paper from CVPR 2017, titled Age Progression/Regression by Conditional Adversarial Autoencoder (Zhang, Song, et al.).
The article presented a method to perform age modification on a given face image, with exciting utilization from recreational applications to assist the searches of missing children.











Link--
http://web.eecs.utk.edu/~zzhang61/docs/papers/2017_CVPR_Age.pdf
